cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the segmentation of prostate from MR images using a convolutional neural network (CNN). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a deeply supervised CNN, which involves passing features extracted from early stages to later stages, indicating the use of deep learning techniques. This makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper deals with medical imaging, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of a neural network for segmentation makes cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category as well.
